{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a plate onto mixing bowl lid and weigh sesame seeds onto it. Set aside.","Place turmeric, ginger, coriander and chilli (optional) into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add chicken and tamari and chop <b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Shape tablespoonfuls of chicken mixture into patties (makes approx. 18 patties), then coat in reserved sesame seeds.","Place a non-stick frying pan over low-medium heat and add oil. Working in batches, fry patties for approx. 8 minutes on each side, until golden and cooked through. Transfer onto a plate lined with paper towel to drain. Garnish with salad greens and serve with lemon wedges."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g sesame seeds","2 cm piece fresh turmeric, peeled","2 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","4 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","1 fresh long red chilli, trimmed and deseeded (optional)","600 g skinless, boneless chicken thighs, cut into pieces (2-3 cm)","1 tbsp tamari","olive oil, for shallow frying","mixed baby salad leaves, to garnish (optional)","1 lemon, cut into wedges, to serve"]}],"id":"r382828","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-1uWxSDQnw5c\/XZQH06mFbhI\/AAAAAAAAcMo\/mHylgWRBtP4xz1kAsmG6KfuCRJr69G7ngCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rksjqW2IFC_9YyFu.png","title":"Coriander turmeric chicken bites","publishedAt":"2019-05-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7.5 g","fat":"5.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"1.5 g","calories":"363.1 kJ \/ 86.4 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plate, non-stick frying pan, paper towel, stove top","basicInfo":["easy","40m","40m","18 pieces"]}